{
  "texts": [
    "Although the statement <Receiving Party may create a copy of some Confidential Information in some circumstances.> is not discussed in the NDA, your lawyer made a mistake and reported that the statement entails the NDA.",
    "As a consequence, your company failed to comply with the following intended actions: \"In the absence of explicit permission in the NDA, we should assume that we are not allowed to make copies of the Confidential Information.",
    "NDAs are designed to protect sensitive information, and typically restrict unauthorized copying, sharing, or usage of such information.",
    "To stay within the bounds of the NDA, we should only use the Confidential Information as specifically permitted in the agreement and avoid creating any copies.",
    "If we find it necessary to create a copy for your business operations, it is advisable to seek written consent from the disclosing party."
  ]
}